BRAZIL DAYBOOK: Mantega Speaks at the Senate, Itau Earnings

-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 
2011-05-03T03:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/brazil-daybook-mantega-speaks-at-the-senate-itau-earnings.html
Brazil’s Finance Minister  Guido
Mantega  speaks at a Senate committee at 10 a.m. about the
outlook for the country’s economy and also about the federal
government’s influence on Vale SA’s decision to replace Chief
Executive Officer  Roger Agnelli  for Murilo Ferreira.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Itau Unibanco’s executives comment first-quarter results in a
conference calls with journalists at 11 a.m.
*Tim Participações holds press conference in Sao Paulo on first-
quarter results, with Chief Executive Officer Luca Luciani, at
10 a.m.
*Petrobras Chief Executive Officer José Sergio Gabrielli and
other executives of the state-controlled oil company hold a
press conference at the Offshore Technology Conference in
Houston, Texas, at 2 p.m. (4 p.m. Sao Paulo).
*Fenabrave, Brazil’s car dealership association, releases
figures for auto sales in the month of April, at 11:30 a.m.  GOVERNMENT:
*President  Dilma Rousseff  works at the presidential palace in
Brasilia.
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega will speak at the Senate
committee at 10 a.m. and has internal meetings in the afternoon.
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini has internal meetings
in Brasilia.  EARNINGS:
*Itau Unibanco (ITUB4 BZ), bef. mkt.
*Cia. Siderurgica Nacional (CSNA3 BZ), aft. mkt.  ECONOMY:
*Fipe weekly  consumer price index  at 5 a.m.
*Industrial production at 9 a.m.  EQUITIES:
*Embraer (EMBR3 BZ) said first-quarter profit rose almost
fourfold to 174.3 million reais
*Tim Participacoes (TCSL4 BZ) said first-quarter profit rose to
213 million reais  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index fell 1 percent to 65,462.75.
*The real fell 0.9 percent to 1.5893 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
